"title": "8498: witnessing, and Holy Spirit",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8498: witnessing, and holy spirit",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Christian witnessing is made effective through the empowering, strengthening and guiding of the Holy Spirit. Witnessing is an aspect of spiritual warfare, and believers need supernatural aid to face Satan's opposition.</p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit supports believers in witnessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:31-Acts5:32\">ACT 5:31–5:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26-John15:27\">JHN 15:26–15:27</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit empowers effective witness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:1-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:1–2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:14-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:14–4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:48-Luke24:49\">LUK 24:48–24:49</a></p>\n<h3>He confirms the testimony of believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:3-Heb2:4\">HEB 2:3–2:4</a></p>\n<h3>He convinces people of their need</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7-John16:11\">JHN 16:7–16:11</a></p>\n<h3>He brings people to new birth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5-John3:8\">JHN 3:5–3:8</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit guides believers in witnessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:39-Acts8:40\">ACT 8:39–8:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:29-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:29–8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:6-Acts16:7\">ACT 16:6–16:7</a></p>\n<h2>Witnessing and spiritual warfare</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:11\">REV 12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:15-Eph6:17\">EPH 6:15–6:17</a></p>\n<h2>Witnessing and persecution</h2>\n<h3>Witnessing results in persecution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:9\">REV 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:17\">ACT 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:40\">ACT 5:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:54-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:54–7:60</a> <em>Stephen's witnessing leads him to become the first Christian martyr. The English word “martyr” comes from the Greek word for “witness”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:22-Acts22:25\">ACT 22:22–22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19-Eph6:20\">EPH 6:19–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:3-Col4:4\">COL 4:3–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:8\">2TI 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:12-Rev2:13\">REV 2:12–2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:9\">REV 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:6\">REV 17:6</a></p>\n<h3>Supernatural help to face persecution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:18-Matt10:20\">MAT 10:18–10:20</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:9-Mark13:11\">MRK 13:9–13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12-Luke21:15\">LUK 21:12–21:15</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:55\">ACT 7:55</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:18-Acts5:19\">ACT 5:18–5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:9-Acts18:10\">ACT 18:9–18:10</a></p>\n<h3>Witness is promoted by persecution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:1-Acts8:5\">ACT 8:1–8:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:12-Phil1:14\">PHP 1:12–1:14</a></p>",
